news.title: Ex-promoters influenced DHFL's share price, paid builder high fee: CBI
news.para: The chargesheet filed ag-ainst the Wadhawans, builder Sanjay Chhabria, Yes Bank founder Rana Kapoor and others claimed that they entered into a criminal conspiracy causing loss to Yes Bank and DHFL for personal gain.

news.title: Ex-promoters of DHFL used many shell companies to divert funds: CBI
news.para: The agency last month booked DHFL, its former chairman and managing director Kapil Wadhawan and director Dheeraj Wadhawan among 14 entities and people on charges of cheating a consortium of 17 banks.

news.title: Grasim forays into B2B e-commerce for building material; to invest Rs 2,000 crore in five years
news.para: Grasim Industries' subsidiary UltraTech Cement is the leading manufacturer of cement in the country with an installed capacity of 119.95 Metric Tonnes Per Annum (MTPA) and had last month announced an investment of Rs 12,886 crore (around USD 1.65 billion) to add 22.6 MTPA capacity.

news.title: Ambuja Cements' net profit falls 25.5% to Rs 865.44 crore in Apr-Jun 2022
news.para: However, its revenue from operations was up 15.11 per cent to Rs 8,032.88 crore during the quarter as compared to Rs 6,978.24 crore in the corresponding quarter of the previous financial year.

news.title: hBits to raise Rs 500-crore alternative investment fund
news.para: The company will be tapping both domestic as well as offshore capital for this fund-raising exercise based on the response to its initial activity in the markets.

news.title: PNB Housing Finance, 12 individuals settle with Sebi a case related to Carlyle deal
news.para: ​The housing finance player, part of state-owned Punjab National Bank, and the 12 individuals, who were directors of the company as on May 31, 2021, jointly paid Rs 72.76 lakh towards settlement.

news.title: HDFC sells shares of Ansal Housing to recover dues
news.para: On June 16, Housing Development Finance Corporation (HDFC Ltd) had informed the exchanges about invocation of 50,00,000 shares of Ansal Housing Ltd, aggregating to 8.42 per cent of its share capital

news.title: Supertech twin towers to be rigged with explosives by Aug 20
news.para: During the period when the explosives would be filled in the skeletal structures of the twin towers, no body except the staff of the demolition firm Edifice Engineering would be allowed inside the premises, according to officials.

news.title: U.S. home builder sentiment plunges, services activity in New York region stalls
news.para: The National Association of Home Builders/Wells Fargo Housing Market Index fell for a seventh straight month to 55, the lowest level since May 2020, from 67 in June, NAHB said in a statement on Monday.

news.title: Shimao Group says receives resumption guidance from Hong Kong stock exchange
news.para: Trading in the shares was suspended on April 1 after the Shanghai-based developer failed to publish its 2021 financial results before the regulatory deadline.

news.title: Fitch cuts China's Guangzhou R&F Properties to 'restricted default'
news.para: R&F received consent from its creditors to extend maturities for $4.9 billion worth of offshore bonds, the latest such move by a Chinese developer to avoid default.

news.title: TCS setting up eight new office spaces that can seat 10,000 staffers each
news.para: They are planned in line with the company’s 25 by 25 model that entails having only 25% of the workforce working from offices for 25% of the time by 2025.

news.title: CBI to produce DHFL's former MD & director in court in Rs 34,815 crore scam case
news.para: The CBI will seek Wadhawans' custody in connection with its FIR related to the scam, they said. Kapil and Dheeraj Wadhawan were in Lucknow in connection with the PF scam also probed by the agency, they said.

news.title: Chennai development body issues lock and seal notices to 720 buildings
news.para: Of these, only 5 percent have carried out rectifications and only one building with violations hgas been demolished. At least 50% of them have gone for appeals and sought time to make rectifications while the rest have not responded to the notice.

news.title: Not verbal, only written pact valid in property purchase: Assam REAT
news.para: Delivering a judgement, Assam REAT Chairperson Justice (Retd) Manojit Bhuyan and Member Onkar Kedia said the terms and conditions of a written contract cannot be modified by any oral agreement.
